The paper deals with the complexity of counting H-colourings, which is a problem in computational complexity theory. The problem is related to counting independent sets in a bipartite graph, which is a well-known problem in computational complexity theory and falls under the category of counting complexity (cs.CC). The paper also uses non-constructive ideas and builds on the work of Lovasz, who is a well-known researcher in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.CG). The problem of counting H-colourings also involves graph theory and combinatorics (cs.DS), and the paper discusses the complexity of the problem in terms of the structure of the input graph H (cs.GT).
